<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-us">
  <head>
    {% include "./head.njk" %}
  </head>
  <body>
    {% include "./header.njk" %}

    <!-- Main section-->
    <div id="main-section" class="container px-4">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="breadcrumb">
          <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
          <li class="breadcrumb-item active">{{title | safe}}</li>
        </ol>
      </nav>
      <main class="row gx-4 justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-10">
          {% block title %}
          <h1>{{title}}</h1>
          {% endblock %}
          <div id="browsers">

            <p>The SkipTo.js browser add-ons and extensions automatically load SkipTo.js on to web pages after the web page is loaded. The "Skip To Content" button is visible after the page completes loading and the extension fives it keyboard focus after the page loads.  Users can open the menu using the <kbd>space</kbd> or <kb>down arrow</kb> key and view/select the landmarks and headings on the page.  If the user moves focus from the button the button slowly fads to the top of the screen, with about 6 pixels of it's bottom border showing.  The menu can be reopened at any time by using the short cut key, <kbd>option</kbd> + <kbd>0</kbd> on the macOS or <kbd>alt</kbd> + <kbd>0</kbd> on Windows and Linux.</p>

            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/skiptojs-for-chrome/bphinmlgdojgihhmppgboipmmjjcfjon">SkipTo.js for Chrome</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-GB/firefox/addon/skipto-js-for-firefox/versions/">SkipTo.js for Firefox</a></li>
            </ul>

          </div>

            {% include "./feedback.njk" %}

          </div>
        </div>
      </main>
    {% include "./footer.njk" %}
    {% include "./scripts.njk" %}

  </body>
</html>
